   "source": [
    "# Fraud Risk Prioritization & Operational Analytics\n",
    "\n",
    "## Business Objective\n",
    "Prioritize high-risk transactions under operational review constraints.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Dataset\n",
    "IEEE-CIS Fraud Detection (Kaggle)\n",
    "\n",
    "## What this notebook shows\n",
    "A business-first walkthrough of preprocessing, modeling, threshold selection, and analyst-facing outputs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39d8f113-b2d9-4320-a367-df16d268eb7e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Problem Context\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud transactions represent ~3.5% of all transactions in the dataset.  \n",
    "Reviewing every transaction is operationally infeasible.\n",
    "\n",
    "The objective is to design a risk scoring framework that:\n",
    "- Ranks transactions by risk\n",
    "- Concentrates fraud into a manageable review queue\n",
    "- Supports threshold decisions based on operational capacity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "81fbf6ce-3f70-4594-a266-149674ed614d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Data Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "Dataset: IEEE-CIS Fraud Detection  \n",
    "Total transactions: ~590,000  \n",
    "Fraud rate: ~3.5%\n",
    "\n",
    "Data includes:\n",
    "- Transaction attributes\n",
    "- Card information\n",
    "- Device and identity variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "03cf5fd2-9d87-4aec-8ed9-24cfb4af9071",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Preprocessing Strategy\n",
    "\n",
    "To simulate real-world deployment:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Performed time-based train/validation split using TransactionDT\n",
    "- Removed ultra-sparse features (>80% missing)\n",
    "- Added missing value indicators\n",
    "- Applied median/mode imputation\n",
    "- Encoded categorical variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1e6687e4-8425-45da-a0a9-4d8d0d5910c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Modeling Approach\n",
    "\n",
    "Used LightGBM (gradient boosting) due to:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Strong performance on tabular data\n",
    "- Ability to handle missing values\n",
    "- Suitability for imbalanced datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "Evaluation focused on:\n",
    "- PR-AUC (better metric for rare fraud cases)\n",
    "- Precision at low review volume\n",
    "- Recall at operational threshold"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7fe3a11f-f5f9-4226-8b1d-281afcab79fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Results\n",
    "\n",
    "- PR-AUC improved from 0.27 → 0.40\n",
    "- >53% precision at 2% review volume\n",
    "- ~58% recall at selected operating threshold (0.10)\n",
    "\n",
    "This demonstrates improved fraud concentration in a small review queue while managing analyst workload."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "03bc2f14-67b4-4ec8-abae-5ea76e994064",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Threshold Decision\n",
    "\n",
    "Selected threshold = 0.10\n",
    "\n",
    "This balances:\n",
    "- Fraud capture (recall)\n",
    "- Review workload (precision)\n",
    "- Operational feasibility"
   ]
  }
 ],
